    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Not sure we want to change the `facetName` behavior, it's more complex to use with an object because you can pass whatever you want.\n\nI think what you want is the ability to add more data to the underlying templates, so maybe we could just do something like:\n\n``` js\nfor facet in facets:\n  myWidget({\n    facetName: facet.name,\n    templatesData: facet,\n    templates: {\n      header: headerTemplate\n  });\n```\n\nor \n\n``` js\nfor facet in facets:\n  myWidget({\n    facetName: facet.name,\n    templates: {\n      header: prepare(headerTemplate, facet) //  replace(/FACET_TITLE/g, facet.title) or something\n  });\n```\n\nWhat do you think?\n",
    "created_at": "2015-10-28T11:06:29Z",
